thread.title_full: On Campus: Edinboro's Caratelli (Blackhawk) has career night in loss

author: Rob Longo Times Sports Correspondent
title: On Campus: Edinboro's Caratelli (Blackhawk) has career night in loss
text:
Edinboro University 
Edinboro wide receiver and Blackhawk graduate Alex Caratelli. 
-- Alex Caratelli (Blackhawk) had a breakout performance for Edinboro in the Fighting Scots’ 49-42 loss to Gannon. Caratelli led all receivers with nine catches for 210 yards and three touchdowns, which came off receptions of 29, 75 and 22 yards. The redshirt sophomore has 29 receptions for 522 yards and five scores this season. Gannon’s Brandon Mansell (Blackhawk) pulled in his first touchdown reception of the season and led the Golden Knights in receiving. Mansell finished the day with seven receptions for 113 yards. 
-- Terry Swanson (Aliquippa) continues to help lead No. 19 Toledo to a spotless record. In Saturday’s 63-20 win over Eastern Michigan, Swanson led the Rockets on the ground with 97 yards on only four carries. One of those rushes was a nine-yard touchdown carry that put Toledo on top early in the second quarter. 
-- Case Western Reserve’s Zech Medved (West Allegheny) scored his first touchdown of the season in Saturday’s 20-7 win at Geneva. The junior tight end had four receptions for 86 yards, both season highs. Tags
